{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783136460,"nonce":"YTKSQgnD8aZAL98lBd5tMmzrj7M=","title":"Split off from SQLite view rendering (39f4468 / PR #74).","message":"The SQLite backend renders views but does not introspect them back\n(`introspect.rs` returns `views: []`). Combined with the core view diff\n(`squealy-model/src/diff.rs::diff_views_global`), which *always* re-emits a\n`CreateView` for a view whose structural body it cannot reconstruct, this means\n**every publish of a model containing a view emits a `CreateView` step ŌĆö even a\nno-op re-publish**. The replan is therefore never empty when a view is present.\n\nTwo consequences:\n\n1. **Churn**: a view-carrying SQLite model never reaches a clean/empty replan.\n   (Pre-existing, cross-backend ŌĆö PostgreSQL/MySQL also re-apply an introspected\n   view every run, via `CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW`. Not SQLite-specific, but more\n   visible once SQLite renders views.)\n\n2. **Data loss (SQLite-specific)**: SQLite has no `CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW`, so\n   the plan applies a `CreateView` as `DROP VIEW IF EXISTS x; CREATE VIEW x ŌĆ”`.\n   `DROP VIEW` in SQLite also drops any `INSTEAD OF` triggers attached to the\n   view (SQLite's mechanism for writeable views). Since squealy does not model\n   triggers, they are not recreated ŌĆö so a no-op publish of a view silently\n   removes user-added triggers and breaks writes through the view. (Verified:\n   `DROP VIEW v` removes the view AND its trigger from `sqlite_master`.)\n   PostgreSQL's `CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW` preserves dependent objects, so it does\n   not have this footgun.\n\n- **Churn-free view replan (core)**: let the diff detect an unchanged view so it\n  emits no step. Needs body-aware comparison (compare rendered SQL against the\n  stored/introspected definition, or reconstruct enough IR to `PartialEq`).\n  Benefits all backends. Largest change; touches `diff_views_global`.\n- **SQLite view introspection**: read view name + columns (and possibly the\n  stored `CREATE VIEW` SQL) from `sqlite_master` (`PRAGMA table_info` works on\n  views) so SQLite reaches the same `(Some, Some)` diff branch as PG/MySQL.\n  Necessary groundwork for the churn-free approach on SQLite.\n- **Trigger preservation (executor, SQLite-specific)**: before a view drop,\n  capture its triggers from `sqlite_master` and replay their `CREATE TRIGGER`\n  statements after recreating the view. Removes the data-loss footgun even if\n  churn remains. Needs trigger-ordering / dependency handling.\n\nViews render (create-from-scratch + incremental plan) with the non-destructive\n`DROP VIEW IF EXISTS` + `CREATE VIEW` form. The churn + trigger-wipe above are\ndocumented in the introspection comment and deferred here.","files":null}]}